caption: It takes Wow factor to earn 5 stars.  Went for the Friday night, reservations only, 3-course meal.  Every course delighted my taste buds and didn't copy anyone else in town!  Hooray for variety and flavorful food! Updated 3/2021: still a mouthful of amazement❣️Itxaso et al (waitstaff) is the perfect example of Basque hospitality. We had yummy wine and food yet again!!

We had a lovely evening at the Basque Market!  Because of covid, we sat outside on their patio which has some propane heaters; it was perfect. The owners Tara and Tony, and their daughter Itxaso, were very welcoming, warm, and friendly and made sure everything was perfect.  We had pinchos, the croquetas, the paella, and the green peppers, and everything was delicious! They also have a great selection of wines by the glass that went extremely well with the food. They also have wine bottles at great prices, which you can either buy to go or drink them on site after you pay a reasonable corkage fee, which we did.  Overall, this was a fantastic experience and can’t wait to visit again!

My wife and I had an incredible experience there for First Thursday. We tried delicious wine, ate delicious food, and enjoyed the atmosphere! The staff was extremely attentive and went above and beyond to give us a fantastic night!
Great little market filled with all kinds of Basque goodies and very friendly staff. I will be back for the paella 👍😋
Amazing tapas at affordable prices. Don't miss this place if passing through Boise.
Absolutely wonderful place.  Extremely kind and generous owners and staff.  Incredible food and wine.  This place is a foodie heaven!

Wow! Way over rated! I feel sorry for people who think this paella is delicious. I could do better at home. Horrible mush with hardly any seafood in it. The food was cold, mushy, and overpriced. I want my money back!

The paella I had was very undercooked. There was no crispy layer and the mussel I got wasn’t even cooked (it was completely closed inside the shell). The rice was still watery and some grains were hard and not cooked. The shrimp and sausage was good
Our first experience with paella and not only was the food delicious the atmosphere and people were very friendly. Our first real dine out since Covid and it was perfect!

Paella is the best we've ever had.  The croquetas are little delicious finger fried bites with savory filling of your choice. Its fun to try and figure out which ones you ordered. They call it the croquetas roulette for a reason. We also had ham and cheese bocadillos along with some tapas. Love the basque cider. No yeast needed to brew. Super crisp and clean to wash everything down. Great selection of Spanish and Basque grocery items. Many wonderful wines. Highly recommend!!!!!!!!!!
Wide choice of good food and drink. Super staff
Cute store selling authentic Basque goods! Got some croquets and paella, which were good too!
Fun morning of investigating and learning,.
An absolutely wonderful shop, old world feel deli with great selection of Spanish and Basque food specialties.
The owners and staff have always treated us like family. This is such a great place for food, or shopping to find a special gift.
Love the place ❤

They make fresh paella in an enormous pan on the street on Wednesday & Friday for lunch and Thursday or dinner, get there right when it's done at noon or you may not get  a plate as  it guess fast! They have pinxtos they are also very authentic & good!
Such an beautiful location. Absolutely love it
Good experience; the staff was friendly; and many of the products are from the Basque Country or local Basque Community.
Nice folks! Had to cancel order and they were very understanding
Some of the most delicious and inspired dishes in Boise!
Great food,  wonderful people, lovely culture.
Attended the cooking class. Great food and met some really nice people.
Had the tapas, which was ok... much prefer ordering from the menu. It can get crowded but the food if delicious.

Great authentic Basque/Spanish tapas.  Fresh-made paella on Wednesdays and Fridays at noon.  Excellent selection of Basque/Spanish wines and gourmet grocery goods. Delicious (sour) Basque cider on tap.
Great food and service. Recommend to everyone
Great time with friends good food great service friendly atmosphere only one thing I didn't care for the cheesecake all else was great
Great 1st Thursday tapas and Wednesday/Friday noon paella.
One of the most unique lunch experiences I've had in the states. Incredible. Great food. Fun atmosphere. Good people. Excellent
One of the best meals I've ever had.
If you can make it here for a tapa happy hour, buy a bottle of wine and park it.
Delicious and gorgeous food
Great selection of pintxos at lunchtime!

Great place. Must visit. The meatballs were out of this world. Get two serves, trust me. The paella pockets were not great - a bit oily and claggy, but still tasty. The wine selection is very f good with a lot of interesting Basque and Spanish wines.
Who doesn't love tapas. Numbering about 16,000, Boise's Basque community is one of the largest such communities in the United States.
Luscious!
I enjoyed this place. My server Jr. was a real knowledgeable guy. Will definitely be going back.
Worth the visit! Cute spot.
Great food, good people in a good easy going atmosphere. Great tapas and paella

On Wednesdays & Fridays transport yourself  to the Basque country on your lunch hour while never leaving Boise. Sample a variety of seasonal tapas: asparagus salad, jambon croquetas, brie and fig jam, olives, grilled peppers, and more. Top it off with a delicate bit of chocolate mousse.  Dine community-style at benches and enjoy the cameraderie of local people. Lovely experience.
Great food family style!

Highly recommend this place. Coming to the basque market before flying out Boise, thus, we didn’t know what to expect. Walked passed by this place to take a gamble and glad we did it as the food is delicious, and very reasonably priced too!
Fabulous small market with really nice tapas and great wine selection. Reminded us of northern Spain. Go for happy hour.

As always, great! I've literally not had a dish I didn't enjoy. The Gateaux is fantastic so save some room to share if dining with others. The people are genuinely just nice and that adds much more to the meal!

I'm sure that I'll be eating here on a regular basis. You can graze on some pintxos or you can get paella a few days a week freshly made right in front of the shop. All sorts of fun drinks and goodies. The Basque block is a great vibe. This is a family operated business and the owners and staff know what hospitality is all about. Take it from someone who knows his paella. Tony and the staff make one of the best tasting paellas anywhere.

Paella was very good on Wednesday. The only thing I didn't like is that I got less meat then other customers because the portions aren't exact but I did want more meat. Wine was good and you can try before you buy and the selection of Pinxtos/Tapas was good! Very kind people and a nice way to spend your lunch relaxing and eating!
Lunch was great and service was excellent! Ready for more Paella in Barcelona this summer:)
Fun atmosphere in long-table group eating setting. We had a very tasty dinner of Basque paella and red wine. Love this place!
What an experience. We had paella for the first time, they cook it right out on the street so everyone for blocks can smell it.  The tapas are a must, great family atmosphere.
Went for the Paella and enjoyed how nice the market is.
Great food and wine 👍
Always a great experience
Great atmosphere and place to nosh on good food.
Really nice selection of olive oils, vinegars, and conservas.

Just another example.of Boise's legacy of accepting people from other lands. What is brought in culturally in the way of foods, customs, dress, becomes accepted as their unique contribution. Many more are still venturing out from their respective states and countries and landing in Boise. I recently saw a T shirt that said I live in Idaho, but I still love Connecticut. I hope they bring a part of their Connecticut roots and graft them to Idaho.

Very good food at very reasonable prices. Excellent paella and tapas. I would recommend the lunch paella or early dinner. It is more moist and fresh. Also early means you will get some and possibly a table. This is a very small place with communal dining. Paella is lunch Weds and Fri and dinner Thurs. Regular menu is daily. Beer and wine from Spain! plus great locals.
Delicious Paella, wine, and tapas in a market setting.
Best food in America. Spanish and basque. The waiter is so nice and so knowledgeable. I came here with a Spanish person, who says its amazing.
Love Pintxos!
Very personable, great service, amazing tapas!
While the food was tasty, the price is a little too high for tapas. Service was a little slow and lacking, despite the fact the place wasn't full.
This place is awesome!!!!

Excellent lunch today at the Basque Market. Our server, Jose, suggested several great tapas all of which were very delicious. The tapas sized portions were more than generous at an excellent price. We loved the frozen sangria with a topping of red wine to accompany our meal. I highly recommend this place.
Excellent food and service !
Food was ok. A bunch of the food wasn’t on the menu tho, also what do you think tapas are.

This is a must stop on any visit to Boise. I usually come for the fresh made paella, currently served Wednesday and Friday at noon. You can watch it be prepared right outside the market. I would recommend coming at least a half hour in advance. Try their wine slushy sangria, topped with red wine, beware of brain freeze. If you come the last weekend in July there is a Basque festival. Live music, food and drinks. The market is small inside but there is seating outside.
Interesting and fun place to visit. The food was good too.

Very good place to have a glass of wine. We had the wine sampler and liked their selections so much we bought a couple of bottles. The food was delicious, the tortilla with mushrooms, and the meatballs were very good. We are definitely going back!

We had an event catered by the Basque Market and I can't recommend them enough! Not only was the food incredible, but the staff we interacted with were so kind and helpful. We were able to see the chef's create the paella and it was delicious. Not to mention, the Piquillo Pepper Cheese was to die for. They even packed up remaining food so attendees could take it home!  Tara and her team were incredibly helpful and responsive to our needs/requests. We went on a tour of the Basque Museum & Cultural Center and also had a special performance by the Oinkari Basque Dancers which was a huge hit with our guests. Such a unique experience and one we will never forget!  If you're in Boise, eating at the Basque Market is a must!
Been here 3 times and every time the food and presentation is phenomenal.  Just go and bring your appititght

This atmosphere is great and the food delicious.  We go for the pintxos (the basque version of tapas). Serving sizes are small as are the prices so you can get a big variety without breaking the bank.  If you’ve never had basque food, you need to try this. You won’t be disappointed.

I did the paella class with my bestie and it was so much fun! Tony and Tara have a great mix of teaching how to make paella and how to have a great time while doing it. We had a wine tasting at the start and more wine throughout (what else do you need, really?). And of course the paella was delicious, but that's to be expected because if you've ever eaten at the Basque Market, you know their food is delicious. Highly recommend!
Basque food is fantastic and this is the place to get the real ingredients.
DELICIOUS.

I want to pack this place up and bring it back to Wisconsin with me! Excellent food, fun atmosphere, and some of the kindest staff I’ve ever met. Plus, a delightful selection of Spanish/Basque wines. Absolutely worth your time!

(Translated by Google) We drive many angry hours for one such experience but the staff. It was not kind we bought a paella dishes and decided to arrive and leave paid then the man arrived who coso the most kind fuel. They did not serve us the paella Very cold  (Original) Conducimos muchas horas enocionados por una experiencia de esas pero el personal. No fue amable compramos un platos de paella y   Decidinos llegar y dejar pagados luego llegamos el hombre que la cosino el fuel mas amable los demas. No nos  sirvieron la paella Muy fria

Very Satisfying experience from the minute I walked in, to the last moment trying to force the final morsel down my throat.  Very attentive and knowledgeable server!  Not knowing the culture or the type of foods to order, the waiter was a plus as he knew exactly what we should order and what we would find enjoyable. The experience was great.  Appetizers we had the Olive dip, the cheese dip and then this really good bacon sweet paradise dip that they made especially for that day, I think it contained goat cheese. Oh my goodness with the baguette it was wonderful.  For the main course. Braised pork loin you can see the picture it was topped with a great balsamic vinegar and it was delicious.  Bread was freshly baked.  You are missing out if you do not pop in here. I highly recommend this place.  Price is super reasonable
Great Pintxos

The Basque Market is a great place to learn about the rich Basque culture of this area. We tried some Basque cuisine; the cheese croquettes were great! Back in 2009, The Basque Market held a function for our convention where they use a gigantic paella pan and cooked for hundreds of people! Apparently they do this at least once a week during the warmer seasons. This last time I was at the market I bought a Basque cookbook. I can't wait to try some recipes.
Authentic Spanish food. I have been to Spain and I felt like I was back there. Worth the trip. We went for lunch so not crowded. Service was great.
Went in between lunch and dinner menus. Got some cheap and delicious tapas from the happy hour list and picked up a few basque goods from their small market area.
The food was very good and authentic.
Great place,  great people!
I think this is a perfect place, with good food, including lunch. Service was terrific. I did go at about 2pm, though.
Delicious Basque fare
Don't miss it.
Fun cooking classes.  Delicious food.
Cute little place with all the best of Spanish cuisine and wines!
Great little Tapas joint and market.  Definitely hit the Paella made on the street and sit outside if the weather permits.  Absolutely loved it here
Good food. A little pricey.
Amazing! Outstanding!
Had awesome paella!  Quaint little restaurant...loved the atmosphere!
Awesome!!!
Nice chill vibe

We had one of the best meals that we have had anywhere in the world last evening at the Basque Market.  The venison tenderloins were fabulous served with a fabulous black eye pea dish. The primi of calamari steak frites and the beautiful dessert, all served with just the right wines made a lovely evening. The service could not have been better.

Very cool place with a great selection of tapas and a small world market. Great selection of small bites and matched wines. Paella served regularly. Small menu of cheese plates and fun items. Friendly staff to help with any questions. Prices were fair and location was perfect in the Basque area. Overall great find that I will return too.
Perfect food and nice service.
Not too bad, but not great.
(Translated by Google) The closest thing to Spain  (Original) Lo más parecido a España

This place had the best Spanish wine I've been able to find in the US! The service was perfect. It is a great atmosphere that feels like being back in Spain and their tapas were delightful! I wish I lived in Boise so I could visit often but it was perfect for a quick stop for wine and pinxtos!
Great staff and variety
Small market, cozy, with a cafe for excellent small bites, sangria, and wine.
I love this place.  Best Riojas anywhere, staff is great!
They are fabulous they are amazing.
Amazing food and knowledgeable,  caring staff.   Love that they have community tables.
Very attentive and friendly service, excellent food (we had 4 or 5 different pinxtos).
Always great food!
Fabulous food.. wonderful staff

We came here for one of our first meals in Idaho, the food and atmosphere was so amazing. The staff was great even though we took over your restaurant with our party of adults and children. The tapas were fantastic and very affordable.  We will definitely be returning on our next visit.
So good food
It's a fun place to eat lunch when they're making a big pan of paella, but go early or you'll miss it.
Great resturaunt with a fantastic atmosphere and friendly people!

This is a great atmosphere, the food is amazing and it is definitely a unique experience here in Boise. The Basque culture is amazing part of our Boise community. I also have to give the staff some additional thank you!!!. After I purchased my food, I accidentally dropped some of my food on the floor. The staff was very friendly and helpful and to my surprise gave me the dish that dropped. I would highly recommend this restaurant!!!
Unbelievably helpful!
Good food! Paella, croquetas, and fried calamari were great!
Paela had a great time
LOVE this place. Tapas were very good, wines were excellent!
The tapas were good and the paella had a good flavor.  We were a bit disappointed that they only had white wine sangria.
Great food and atmosphere.
Amazing experience, food was good
A place you must visit if you come to Boise. Come hungry.
Incredibly friendly staff, strong drinks from YouTube trained bartender along with the best lamb shanks I've tasted in quite a while.  Worth a trip.
Great lunch spot! We also love their cooking classes.

Great ponchos and friendly knowledgeable staff. If you are there on a paella day I highly reccomend it. I have traveled around Spain many times and the paella I had there was very good. They even have txakoli which can be difficult to find (at least in Seattle).

Wow! What a gem. Here on Friday night for rotating dinner menu. It was delicious and filling. Choice of appetizer, entrée and dessert. All delicious! I recommend highly. Great Spanish wine menu. Incredible! I would highly recommend giving it a try!
(Translated by Google) Ahhhhhh. A Must  (Original) Ahhhhhh. A Must
Went there for cooking class . It was amazing . Food and owners can't say enough good things about them.  Love this place and will return .
I had never had tapas before...very good, and great service!
Good food. Good city.
This is THE place in the valley for Basque food. The paella great, but you better come early.
Great place to eat & shop if Basque is your thing. It's a great addition to have in Boise!
Lysa was very helpful and it was a wounderdul experience.

I have gone back and forth on weather or not to leave a review. At the end of day I have been in the service industry for almost 20 years. I feel like this needs to be said. My mom and I went to the Basque Market for the first time on June …
The paella on Wednesdays is great, definitely recommend trying it.
The dinners are amazing!
Love this place! Amazing food. Take one of the classes! Super fun.

Very tasty - we had a variety of different things.  The almonds and olives were my favorite, though the sangria was very good as well.  I'm not sure what was on the small sandwich I tried, possibly some kind of puree made from olives?  It was delicious though, wish I'd had room for another.  I'd never tried flan before and was pleasantly surprised.  I'll definitely go back next time we're in Boise.
The sangria was delicious. We just did a very lite lunch and just got a few items from the small plates lunch buffet. The service is great and we'd definitely return
Go for fresh paella on Wednesday and Friday at lunchtime.
Nice selection of wine and foods. Helpful service.
Love the ambiance of the Basque Block!
Quality overall is wonderful!
Nice people and great food!
(Translated by Google) Beautiful place,  (Original) Precioso lugar,

Really good experience. Im from Spain and I felt really close to home. The tapas were tasty and creative and the paella was really good too. They have real cider from northern Spain (at least the same flavor you will find in Asturias, Cantabria and Basque country), which is something I miss from Spain. They had really good flan too. The waiter gave us space (for some people would be ignoring you) and didnt rush us at all, unlike the fast paced service typical in America.  I highly recommend.
Wonderful tapas.
Paella was perfect.

I came here with a friend and they were basically ignoring me and my bff.  The waitress left hair in our food and took our bread when we pointed it out. Later on they were incredibly bitchy towards my pregnant friend. Horrible place to eat.

My wife and I are visiting Boise from Denver. I thought our lunch was absolutely wonderful. The service, the wine and the food were all exceptional. We were lucky enough to walk in on one of two days they serve paella. Oh so good.
The best food!!
Always amazing food and a wonderful staff. The wines not bad either ;-)

I bought two group cooking classes as a gift for my mom and signed up to the paella class on April 19th. We were really excited to go together, but the night before my grandmother spent the whole night in the hospital with pneumonia. My mom stayed with her and didn't get any sleep. My mom said she was really tired and asked me to see if we could switch days. I told The Basque Market about our extenuating circumstances and they did not seem to care at all. They said they could not let us attend another group lesson.
Great food
Good selection of Basque food, wine and serving pieces.

intriguing Basque market with helpful staff. The outside seating was a treat for lunch, combined with outstanding cheeses, excellent tapas sized servings. Meals are a bit light-which is my preference.
Tapas, cider, and pallela. What's not to love?
Fun block, great history
Great Basque and Spanish fare, awesome paella. A bit too small and uncomfortable though for a sit-down restaurant.

Small shop so get in early or call ahead if you are looking for one of their quickly selling items. One of the pluses at the Basque Market is the knowledgeable person who always seems to be on site; no pretentiousness exhibited when I ask newb cheese (etc.) questions.
There food was so fresh,  and so yummy...  Unlike the other two Basque restaurants on that block this place lived  up to the Basque standards,  Everything that we had here was world class...
Very cool, quaint old historical Basque market located in the historical district of downtown Boise.

We really enjoyed our little lunch at this charming market.  In addition to some very hard to find condiments, they offer a range of beautiful items the cooks in your will be sure to enjoy.  The staff was both helpful and friendly..  Be sure to try the Rice Pudding.
DELIGHTFUL!!  Staff is unsurpassed;  food and atmosphere, great!  good food, company, and always learn something new!
